Police spokesperson FC van Wyk said the two were embroiled in an argument when the suspect allegedly stabbed the man in the back with a knife. The incident happened on the corner of Voortrekker Road and Jakes Gerwel Drive. “The two attendants were arguing over a possible passenger when the deceased was stabbed in the back with a knife. “The suspect jumped into a Toyota Quantum and fled the scene. “The deceased died on the scene. “The investigating officer, Sergeant Bongani Nkombisa, led the arrest of a 19-year-old suspect at about 6.45pm, at an address in Boskloof Road, Tafelsig, Mitchells Plain. “The murder weapon was recovered from the Quantum on which the suspect was working at the time,” Van Wyk said. The 19-year-old is expected to appear in the Goodwood Magistrate’s Court soon on a charge of murder. Cape Times